  <body> 
    <%= render 'header' %>
    
    <div id="container" class="js-close-any" canvas="container">
      <div id="wrapper">
        <div class="row">
            <h3 class="title">Frequently asked questions</h3>
        </div>
        
        <div class="row left one-margin-bottom center">
          <div class="small-12 medium-8 small-centered columns">
            <ul class="accordion" data-accordion>
              <li class="accordion-navigation">
                <a href="#q1">My time is more valuable than the average person's. Shouldn't I get more Currents for my time?</a>
                <div id="q1" class="content">
                  Fair argument, but 1 hour of your time is the cost to create and earn 1 Current. If you don't think openCurrents is worth your time, no one is forcing you to participate. Others are already giving their time and happily accepting the offer.
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="accordion-navigation">
                <a href="#q2">What prevents people from being lazy and still earning currency while "on the clock"?</a>
                <div id="2q" class="content">
                  Organizations are not required to issue Currents for hours that a volunteer gives. It doesn't cost the business or nonprofit to give Currents, so typically the organization will be happy to reward its volunteers. However, if a volunteer is free-riding, he or she is a burden on employees. The organization can ask a volunteer to move on by no longer validating Currents.
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="accordion-navigation">
                <a href="#q3">Accordion 3</a>
                <div id="q3" class="content">
                  
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        
      <div id="push"></div>
    
      <!-- wrapper div-->
      </div>
      
      <%= render "footer" %>
      
    <!--container div -->
    </div>
    
    <div id="bottom-stripe" class="full-width"></div>
    
    <div off-canvas="menu right shift" id="menu">
      <%= render 'menu' %>
    </div>
  
    <div id="-popup" class="modal center small-12 medium-9 large-7 small-centered columns">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="center small-centered medium-10 columns">
          <h3 class="one-margin-bottom"></h3>
          
          <p></p>
          
          <button class="tax-id-popup_close button round">Okay</button>
          <a><button class="button round secondary"></button></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    
    <script type="text/javascript">
      $(document).ready(function(){
        $('#change-email').popup({
          vertical: 'top',
          transition: 'all 0.75s',
          scrolllock: true,
        });
      });
    </script>
    
    <script>
      $(document).foundation({
        accordion: {
          callback : function (accordion) {
            console.log(accordion);
          }
        }
      });
    </script>
    
    <script>
      ( function ( $ ) {
        // Initialize Slidebars
        var controller = new slidebars();
        controller.init();
      } ) ( jQuery );
    </script>

    <script>
      // Initialize Slidebars
      var controller = new slidebars();
      controller.init();

      // Toggle Slidebars
      $( '.toggle-menu' ).on( 'click', function ( event ) {
        // Stop default action and bubbling
        event.stopPropagation();
        event.preventDefault();

        // Toggle the Slidebar with id 'id-1'
        controller.toggle( 'menu' );
        
        // Close any
        $( document ).on( 'click', '.js-close-any', function ( event ) {
          if ( controller.getActiveSlidebar() ) {
            event.preventDefault();
            event.stopPropagation();
            controller.close();
          }
        } );
      } );
    </script>
  </body>
</html>